        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:24PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
North Carolina Zoo, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Siler City, Liberty, Ramseur, Franklinville, Staley, Snow Camp,
Coleridge, Hasty, and Sutphin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
